test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 1 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7fde34c5e140>([3])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7fde34c5e140> = [[1, 3, 3], [3], [1, 3, 3], [3], [1, 3], [3]].count
 +  and   1 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7fde34c5e140>([1, 3])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7fde34c5e140> = [[1, 3, 3], [3], [1, 3, 3], [3], [1, 3], [3]].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 9 == 3
 +  where 9 = <built-in function prod>([1, 3, 3])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
